    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Foams used to provide structure in packaging or for other applications such as furniture. Structural  foams can be produced by injecting gases into a molten thermoplastic under pressure in an extruder.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000028681/Agranoff, ed., Modern Plastics Encyclopedia (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>可在包裝過程或其他如家具等應用領域，提供結構支撐的泡沫。結構泡沫可透過在熔融的熱塑性塑膠中注入氣體，再以壓力經過擠壓噴嘴製成。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
